    "body": "Hey @NawfelBengherbia, thanks for the ideas! These sound good, although the names may need adjustment to be consistent with the rest of the libraries e.g. `then` would be called `chain` to match `Option` and `Result` (just for reference, there is a proposal to change these names: https://github.com/mozilla/rust/issues/7294).\n\n---\n\nAlso, a Github tip: if you wrap code blocks like so:\n\n``````\n```rust\nfn some_code() { ... }\n```\n``````\n\nThen they will get rendered as code (with Rust syntax highlighting)! (I edited your comment and the issue to add these two lines in. :) )\n",
