    "body": "Im currently working on a future/promise library for rust. Like @brson suggested its a thin policy layer on top of channels with read/write once guarantees and a few methods for creating and transforming futures. I just started the development so any feedback or PRs are more then welcome. Please let me know what you think and if this would be a good replacement for the current `std::sync::Future`.\n\nhttps://github.com/lucidd/rust-promise\n",
